$LCID I believe that other EV companies and their investors owe TSLA a huge debt of gratitude for paving the way. Were they perfect in their execution? Of course not. They moved relatively fast and broke things, a la Facebook, but they proved there is room in the marketplace for EVs. A decade ago that certainly was not as clear as it is today.

Recent observations about many TSLA bulls is that they are now afraid of competition and try to make it out as of there is only room for one player in this field. Fundamentally, their competitors believe there is room for many companies in this burgeoning niche. There definitely are enough dollars for there not to be a winner take all situation. EVs account for around 2% of the market.

That said, what is more likely to happen from an investment returns viewpoint: TSLA doubles in value to over $1.5T in the next year or two, or LCID, GGPI, or another company’s market cap 2X’s? I am betting on the latter happening first. Bullish
